Ganesha, or Ganesa is the Hindu God of Learning and Wisdom.  This Hindu God has animal characteriastics.  He has the head of an Elephant, described as "the wisest of beasts", and is usually represented as accompanied by a rat, a creature regarded as being almost equally wise and cunning.  He might also be described as a God of beginnings, as few projects were set on foot or journeys entered upon without invoking him.